crontab -l --> to view all cron jobs 
crontab -e --> edit cron edit file 
0 12 *** echo "backup complete " >> file   ---> this will every day at 12 pm append back up complete to a file 
at --> automate one time tasks from a certain amount of minutes from now 
at now + 1 minute --> waits for your imput end with [ Ctrl +D ] 
atq -> view pending at jobs 
atrm (job id ) --> delete a scheduled at job 
need to use |  between the comands to add at
type ctrl D when done

